Microsoft Corporation


    CERTIFICATE AS TO PARTIES, RULINGS
    AND RELATED CASES
A.    Parties and Amici
        The following is a list of all parties,
intervenors and amici who have appeared before the United
States District Court for the District of Columbia and all
parties, intervenors and amici in this Court: United States of
America (Plaintiff-Appellant), Microsoft Corporation
(Defendant-Appellant), I.D.E. Corporation (Amicus Curiae),
Anonymous Amici Represented by Gary L. Reback, Esq. of
Wilson, Sonsini, Goodrich & Rosati (Amici Curiae) and
Computer & Communications Industry Association (Amicus
Curiae).
        Microsoft Corporation has no parent
companies, subsidiaries or affiliates that have issued shares or
debt securities to the public.
B.    Rulings Under Review
        The following is a list of the rulings at
issue in this Court: (i) the Order re Motion to Approve the
Consent Decree of the Honorable Stanley Sporkin dated
February 14, 1995 (J.A. 1190-91); (ii) the Order re Motions to
Participate and Motion to Strike of the Honorable Stanley
Sporkin dated February 14, 1995 (J.A. 1192-93) (reported at
United States v. Microsoft Corp., No. 94-1564, 1995 WL
60545 (D.D.C. Feb. 14, 1995)); and (iii) the Memorandum
Opinion of the Honorable Stanley Sporkin dated February 14,
1995 (J.A. 1194-1238) (reported at United States v. Microsoft
Corp., 94-1564, 1995 WL 59480 (D.D.C. Feb. 14, 1995)). The
above Orders and Memorandum Opinion have not been
published in any official reporter.
C.    Related Cases
        This case has not previously been before
this Court or any other court. There are no related cases.

