<P>A: That's correct.</P>

<P>Q: And when you would go jogging on the streets of Little Rock, quite often, unlike today, sir, you had a lot more personal freedom, did you not, as far as being able to move without the necessary requirements of security?</P>

<P>A: Yes. And particularly if I was downtown in daylight, I would run sometimes on Main Street, that was one of the streets I regularly ran on.</P>

<P>Q: Okay. And you were free to run on your own and to go out and run and go by and visit people and talk to people and the like?</P>

<P>A: That's correct.</P>

